  "market_context": "Light Crude Oil Futures (CL1!) on 8 February 2024. Price had been in a rising sequence during the Asian and early London sessions, sweeping a prior high during the London kill zone (02:00–05:00 EST), setting up a bearish daily profile (Open-High-Low-Close).",
  "key_observation": "During London (02:00–05:00 EST), price swept a swing high and printed a series of up-close candles. A close below that series confirmed a Change in State of Delivery to bearish. At 08:30 NY open, price made a brief manipulation run higher into the resulting order block, providing the short entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified the bearish daily profile expectation (Open-High-Low-Close) on the 15-minute CL1! chart for 8 February 2024.",
    "Step 2: Observed that during the London session (02:00–05:00 EST), price swept a prior swing high, forming a series of up-close candles.",
    "Step 3: Confirmed a Change in State of Delivery (CHoCH) when price closed below the series of up-close candles on the 30-minute chart, marking those candles as an order block.",
    "Step 4: Dropped to the 5-minute chart to monitor the New York session open at 08:30 EST.",
    "Step 5: At 08:30, observed price consolidate then make a manipulation run higher (opposing move) back into the order block formed by the series of up-close candles, now acting as a propulsion block.",
    "Step 6: Entered a short position when price closed below the order block on the 5-minute chart, placing the stop-loss above the 08:30 manipulation high.",
    "Step 7: Targeted 2R as the take-profit; observed the trade tag in, retest the propulsion block, and deliver to the 2R target during the New York session.",
    "Step 8: Zoomed back out to the 15-minute chart to confirm that London formed the wick of the daily candle and New York continued lower, completing the Open-High-Low-Close daily candle structure."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit 2R target during the New York session. London formed the daily candle's high (wick), and New York continued lower, completing the bearish Open-High-Low-Close daily profile.",
  "lessons": "When London sweeps a high and a Change in State of Delivery is confirmed, wait for the 08:30 NY open manipulation run higher into the order block before entering short. The propulsion block retest provides a high-probability entry with a defined stop above the manipulation high, targeting 2R.",
